  "excerpt": "<p>Update Status for Salesforce Dashboards and Reports 1. Click on a dashboard or report name to open the Info-Window 2. Select the Analytics Status Bulk Edit Status for Salesforce Dashboards and Reports DataTools Pro allows you to bulk select Dashboards and Reports so you can bulk update status. To complete this task: 1. Select the [&hellip;]</p>",
  "content_html": "\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-2 gb-2-col-equal\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p>DataTools Pro simplifies the process of tracking a Salesforce dashboard lifecycle using a simple status field.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Production</strong>: Reports and dashboards actively used by business units or individuals.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>In Progress/Development</strong>: Reports still being built, tested, or validated.</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Deprecated</strong>: Reports that are no longer used and should be flagged for removal.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Want to add a custom status for your process?</strong> <a href=\"/contact\" title=\"\">Feel free to contact us</a></p>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"e7edf2\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #e7edf2;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"401\" height=\"425\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-42-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10386 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-42-png.webp 401w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-42-283x300.webp 283w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 401px) 100vw, 401px\" /></figure>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio\"><div class=\"wp-block-embed__wrapper\">\n<div class=\"ratio ratio-16x9\"><iframe loading=\"lazy\" title=\"Manage Salesforce Dashboard Lifecycle with Status\" width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/-MKLEpGaSGc?feature=oembed\" frameborder=\"0\" allow=\"accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share\" referrerpolicy=\"strict-origin-when-cross-origin\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n</div></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Update Status for Salesforce Dashboards and Reports</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Click on a dashboard or report name to open the Info-Window</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"8c8e8f\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #8c8e8f;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"689\" height=\"336\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-43-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10387 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-43-png.webp 689w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-43-300x146.webp 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 689px) 100vw, 689px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Select the Analytics Status</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Bulk Edit Status for Salesforce Dashboards and Reports</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>DataTools Pro allows you to bulk select Dashboards and Reports so you can bulk update status. To complete this task:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. Select the first report or dashboard for your desired bulk selection</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f5f9f8\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f5f9f8;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"842\" height=\"402\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-44-png.webp\" alt=\"select Salesforce Dashboard\" class=\"wp-image-10388 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-44-png.webp 842w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-44-300x143.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-44-768x367.webp 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 842px) 100vw, 842px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-columns gb-layout-columns-2 gb-2-col-equal\"><div class=\"gb-layout-column-wrap gb-block-layout-column-gap-2 gb-is-responsive-column\">\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p>2.&nbsp;<strong>Bulk select additional records 1 by 1:</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Hold the&nbsp;<strong>Ctrl&nbsp;</strong>button on your keyboard and click on the individual records that you would like to bulk edit</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f0f7f5\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f0f7f5;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"389\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-45-1024x389.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10389 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-45-1024x389.webp 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-45-300x114.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-45-768x292.webp 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-45-png.webp 1058w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"wp-block-genesis-blocks-gb-column gb-block-layout-column\"><div class=\"gb-block-layout-column-inner\">\n<p>2.&nbsp;<strong>Bulk select records in sequence from first selected</strong></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Hold the&nbsp;<strong>Shift&nbsp;</strong>button on your keyboard and click the last record in sequence that you would like to select. DataTools will auto-select all records in between.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-large\"><img data-dominant-color=\"edf6f4\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #edf6f4;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"1024\" height=\"444\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-46-1024x444.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10390 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-46-1024x444.webp 1024w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-46-300x130.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-46-768x333.webp 768w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-46-png.webp 1075w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px\" /></figure>\n</div></div>\n</div></div>\n\n\n\n<p>3. Click on the “Edit X Reports” button</p>\n\n\n\n<p>4. Select the Status dropdown</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img data-dominant-color=\"f3f6f6\" data-has-transparency=\"false\" style=\"--dominant-color: #f3f6f6;\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"807\" height=\"274\" src=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-47-png.webp\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-10391 not-transparent\" srcset=\"https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-47-png.webp 807w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-47-300x102.webp 300w, https://datatoolspro.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/11/image-47-768x261.webp 768w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 807px) 100vw, 807px\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>5. Select 1 Status.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>6. Press “Assign Status” to bulk assign the status.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>7. Close the window by clicking the close icon or click outside of the popup window.</p>\n"
}